events.name: San Antonio Spurs at Miami Heat

headlines.description: — Gregg Popovich got the perfect anniversary gift from his San Antonio Spurs.
headlines.shortLinkText: On Popovich's coaching anniversary, Spurs top Heat 115-111

headlines.description: — Brooklyn Nets coach Jacque Vaughn mixed up his lineup and his defenses Saturday night — and the nine players in uniform responded.
headlines.shortLinkText: Thomas helps short-handed Nets rally past Pacers, 136-133

headlines.description: — John Wall stole the ball and then sank a jumper, and although he was a member of the visiting team now, the fans in Washington still sounded impressed.
headlines.shortLinkText: Clippers edge Wizards 114-107 in Wall's return to Washington

events.name: Oklahoma City Thunder at Cleveland Cavaliers

headlines.description: — Caris LeVert scored 22 points, Evan Mobley had 21 points and 12 rebounds and the Cleveland Cavaliers never trailed in a 110-102 victory over the Oklahoma City Thunder on Saturday night.
headlines.shortLinkText: LeVert scores 22 points, Cavaliers beat Thunder 110-102

headlines.description: — DeMar DeRozan had 28 points and nine rebounds and the Chicago Bulls took advantage of NBA scoring leader Luka Doncic's absence to rout the Dallas Mavericks 144-115 on Saturday night.

events.name: Boston Celtics at Golden State Warriors

headlines.description: — Six months later, the Splash Brothers were still feeling it from all over the court against the Celtics and delivered one of their team's signature wins of the season so far.
headlines.shortLinkText: Thompson scores 34, Warriors beat Celtics in Finals rematch

headlines.description: — Nikola Jokic had 31 points, 14 assists and 12 rebounds in his 80th career triple-double, and the Denver Nuggets held off the undermanned Utah Jazz 115-110 on Saturday night.
headlines.shortLinkText: Jokic scores 31 in triple-double, Nuggets top depleted Jazz

events.name: Minnesota Timberwolves at Portland Trail Blazers

headlines.description: — Damian Lillard had 36 points and eight assists, Anfernee Simons added 31 points and the Portland Trail Blazers beat the Minnesota Timberwolves 124-118 on Saturday night.
headlines.shortLinkText: Lillard has 36 points, Trail Blazers beat Timberwolves
